{
  "name": "RPlog_Flight_of_the_Corellian",
  "title": "Flight of the Corellian",
  "summary": "The archaeologist Paul Nighman and his young companion Shenner are picked up at a spaceport by the newly retired Admiral Jeralic Mandragon, who ferries them by Lambda shuttle toward Tatooine at Ackbar's request. During the multi-jump journey, Paul confides his worry over his missing colleague Marcus, who borrowed his ship the Bolt for a secretive excavation and has fallen out of contact, leaving Paul ship-less and uneasy. To pass the time and distract himself, Paul lets Shenner watch and help with the hyperspace navigation while drawing out her story: how the bounty hunter Grathix recruited her on Tatooine, the plot to fake the assassination of Etti IV's leader Simone Drake as a distraction in a hunt for Han Solo, and how she instead fell in with Luke Skywalker after he saved her from a lurking attacker, ending up aboard the Alderaan. After a Mon Cal cruiser checkpoint and several jumps, they land on the hated dustball of Tatooine, where Jeralic agrees to stay with the shuttle for the duration. Paul and Shenner prepare to head into Mos Eisley to find Grathix and pursue the archaeological assignment that may take them to Mandalore.",
